        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "In the Zend_View Docs at (Version 1.10):\r\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.view.introduction.html\r\n\r\nit says:\r\n\"encoding: indicate the character encoding to use with htmlentities(), htmlspecialchars(), and other operations. Defaults to ISO-8859-1 (latin1). May be set via setEncoding() or the encoding  option to the constructor. \"\r\n\r\nIn the advisory at:\r\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/security\/advisory\/ZF2010-01\r\n\r\nit says:\r\n\"The afore-mentioned [Zend_View] classes have been reworked to use a default character encoding of UTF-8...a decision was made to default to UTF-8 for the internal encoding mechanisms used by Zend_View. \"\r\n\r\nThese two documents seem to be conflicting.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nAlthough, looking into my Zend_View object (version 1.9.8) it appears that it does default to UTF-8 - so the Documentation for Zend View is more likely to be the wrong one.\r\n\r\n\r\n{code} \r\nabstract class Zend_View_Abstract implements Zend_View_Interface\r\n{\r\n    ...\r\n\r\n    \/**\r\n     * Encoding to use in escaping mechanisms; defaults to utf-8\r\n     * @var string\r\n     *\/\r\n    private $_encoding = 'UTF-8';\r\n\r\n    ...\r\n{code} \r\n\r\n"
        },
